(202, 1, '2019-03-31 15:20:09', '2019-03-31 15:20:09', 'Now that you have learned the first step of Javascript, it is time for some further improvements to yourself by checking out the following features and vital elements of Javascript.\n\n1. Javascript is originally known Livescript and then as ECMASCRIPT .\n\n2. Javascript extension is <strong>.js</strong>\n\n3. Javascript can be placed in either body, head, both body &amp; head and external file ( then place the linking in the head section)\n\nlike , within <strong>&lt;body&gt;...&lt;/body&gt;</strong> , <strong>&lt;head&gt;...&lt;/head&gt;</strong> and any external file with <strong>.js </strong>extension\n\n4. Javascript is case sensitive i.e for example the words <strong>\'JAvascript\',</strong> <strong>\'javascRipT\'</strong> &amp; <strong>\'javascript\'</strong> are all different.\n\n5. Javascript is a client side scripting language i.e. they can\'t directly interact with the server.\n\n6. Javascript is complementarily implemented with HTML majorly along with other languages.\n\n7. Javascript is one of the most primary, lightweight and fastest programming languages available in the market.\n\nSo, with these very given basics we can surely rush into the next chapter where we see the variables, datatypes and other conventions of javascript.', 'Learn Javascript - A few things to Remember', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '199-autosave-v1', '', '', '2019-03-31 15:20:09', '2019-03-31 15:20:09', '', 199, 'http://www.rajdeeproy.com/199-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
